  "title": "Chemical Technician- 12 hours shift",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Perform daily batch processes in accordance to SOP and comply strictly to safety, quality and environmental guidelines.</li>\n  <li>Perform equipment line-ups and operate reactors in accordance to established practices and procedures.</li>\n  <li>Charge chemicals into reactor manually.</li>\n  <li>Carry out drumming operations as and when required.</li>\n  <li>Report all process/equipment/environmental abnormalities, incidents and/or near misses to Shift Superintendent/Engineer/Production Manager. Take part in further investigation when required.</li>\n  <li>Adhere to Company and departmental procedures, SHEQ rules and regulations, and GMP at all times.</li>\n  <li>Carry out scheduled housekeeping activities.</li>\n  <li>Ensure proper handover and takeover during shift changes.</li>\n  <li>Participate as CERT member.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>ITE Certificate/ Diploma in Engineering (Chemical), Engineering (Industrial), Engineering (Material Science), Engineering (Mechanical), Engineering (Petroleum/Oil/Gas) or equivalent.</li>\n  <li>Relevant working experience in chemical industries.</li>\n  <li>On-the-job raining will be provided for entry level.</li>\n  <li>An effective team player with good communication skills.</li>\n  <li>Must be able to work on 12-hours rotating shift in Jurong Island.</li>\n  <li>Remuneration will commensurate with qualifications and experience.</li>\n</ul>",
